title: HPI Spencer
content: The patient presents with a right middle finger crush injury that occurred on 7-8-25 when her finger was crushed by a dumbbell. She experienced immediate pain, swelling, and limited motion. She sought urgent care where X-rays revealed a fracture, and she was treated with a splint. Follow-up X-rays after 4 weeks showed continued fracture, leading her to continue wearing the splint. She now presents for further evaluation and treatment.

title: Musculoskeletal
content: Some hematoma noted, excellent flexion of the PIP, some DIP stiffness, no tenderness on palpation of the distal phalanx, some paresthesia at the distal phalanx.

title: Imaging Results
content: X-rays show a fracture of the distal phalanx with stable alignment and good fracture healing.

title: Plan
content: Reple advanced activity, avoid hanging from hands, return to clinic in 3 weeks for nail check before wedding.
